OL,3,CHow have our councils responded
OL,4,Cfollowing the asylum hotel court
OL,5,Cruling?
OL,7,FAsylum accommodation is just one of
OL,8,Ftheir many potential uses, but under
OL,9,Fnational planning rules, only those
OL,10,FHMOs with seven bedrooms or more
OL,11,Frequire planning permission from the
OL,12,Frelevant local authority ` in
OL,13,FLancashire's case, the dozen district
OL,14,Fcouncils or the standalone authorities
OL,15,Fin Blackpool and Blackburn with Darwen.
OL,17,FSmaller HMOs are deemed 'permitted
OL,18,Fdevelopment', meaning they do not have
OL,19,Fto go through the planning system `
OL,20,Fand so no record of their creation
OL,21,Fexists.
